DOCUMENTATION\
\
Added date element, with specifier for day of the week which has an optional normalization into ISO.\
Added the weather element, with attribute for normalized World Meteorological Organization codes.\
Added the quote element, which distinguishes between direct (speech) and scare (commentary) quotes.\
Added the optional @running-quote to <quote> for when quotes run across paragraph breaks, to ensure they complete each other. Naming convention is the @n of the two paragraphs it runs between (i.e., p002/p003)\
Broke <place> out of <p> for better control, specifically to add in alternate spellings via <alternate>.\
Added marginalia element for extratextual content. Controlled attributes for location of content.\
Added title element, for media or corporation titles which may or may not have authority records.\
Added person element, with optional role attributes.\
Added certainty attribute to measure reliability of correction or expansion. Referenced the certainty-attribute definition within <expan> and <corr> as part of <alternates>.\
Nested the above within <p> as child elements for formatting.\
Removed page number designator text in lieu of <pb>.}